The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                    The City Diary

        Mayor Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharyya wants police to take immediate steps to remove hawkers from carriageways. The mayor expressed his wish at a meeting with additional police commissioner K. Harirajan at the civic headquarters on Friday. An official said the hawker unions have reneged on their commitment not to encroach on carriageways and not to sit with wares within 50 ft of major crossings. 
  The father of an 11-year-old girl has alleged that his daughters right leg had to be amputated because of the negligence of doctors at NRS Medical College. Anindita Barik, a resident of East Midnapore, was admitted to the hospital in November with meningitis. As the drip could not be administered through her arms, it was done through her right leg. Aninditas father Satyabrata Barik alleged on Friday that her right leg had been infected two weeks ago and was amputated. The hospital said a probe would be ordered.
  An abandoned briefcase triggered a bomb scare at the airport around 9.45am on Friday. The briefcase, spotted near the arrival gate of the domestic terminal, was found to contain documents. 
                                                                           
